  "text": "The envoyproxy/envoy repository implements gRPC health check protocol compliance through several key components:\n\n## Core gRPC Health Checker Implementation\n\nThe primary implementation is located in `source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/health_checker_impl.h` and `.cc`, which implements the `GrpcHealthCheckerImpl` class and the nested `GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession`. This implementation:\n\n1. **Handles grpc.health.v1.Health Service**: Uses the gRPC health check protocol defined in `src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.proto` (from grpc/grpc repository). The health checker factory (`GrpcHealthCheckerFactory`) creates health checkers and references the `grpc.health.v1.Health.Check` method via `Protobuf::DescriptorPool::generated_pool()->FindMethodByName(\"grpc.health.v1.Health.Check\")`.\n\n2. **HealthCheckRequest Handling**: In `onInterval()` method (line 186-239), creates and serializes a `grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckRequest` with optional service name field, sends it via gRPC, and uses `Grpc::Common::serializeToGrpcFrame()` for proper gRPC frame encoding.\n\n3. **HealthCheckResponse Status Mapping**: \n   - In `decodeData()` (line 130-162), deserializes the `grpc::health::v1::HealthCheckResponse` protobuf message from the gRPC frame\n   - In `isHealthCheckSucceeded()` (line 300-312), maps the response status enum to health decisions:\n     - `SERVING` (value 1) = healthy\n     - `NOT_SERVING` (value 2) = unhealthy  \n     - `SERVICE_UNKNOWN` (value 3) = unhealthy\n     - `UNKNOWN` (value 0) = unhealthy\n   - In `logHealthCheckStatus()` (line 365-398), logs the health response status for debugging\n\n4. **gRPC Protocol Compliance**: \n   - `decodeHeaders()` (line 96-128) validates HTTP/2 responses and implements HTTP-to-gRPC status mapping per RFC 7540 compliance requirements\n   - `decodeTrailers()` (line 164-174) extracts gRPC status codes from trailers\n   - Uses `Grpc::Common::getGrpcStatus()` to retrieve status from headers/trailers\n   - Uses `Grpc::Utility::httpToGrpcStatus()` for HTTP status code mapping\n\n## gRPC Protocol Utilities\n\n`source/common/grpc/status.h` and `.cc` implement HTTP-to-gRPC status code mapping (`Utility::httpToGrpcStatus()` at line 6-26 of status.cc) following the official gRPC specification at https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/master/doc/http-grpc-status-mapping.md:\n- 400 → INTERNAL\n- 401 → UNAUTHENTICATED\n- 403 → PERMISSION_DENIED\n- 404 → UNIMPLEMENTED\n- 429, 502, 503, 504 → UNAVAILABLE\n- Other → UNKNOWN\n\n`source/common/grpc/common.h` provides essential protocol utilities:\n- `isGrpcResponseHeaders()` - validates gRPC response header compliance\n- `getGrpcStatus()` - extracts gRPC status codes from headers/trailers\n- `getGrpcMessage()` - retrieves gRPC status messages\n\n`source/common/grpc/codec.h` handles gRPC frame encoding/decoding with proper compression flag handling.\n\n## Health Discovery Service (HDS)\n\n`source/common/upstream/health_discovery_service.h` and `.cc` implement a gRPC-based health check reporting system that communicates health check results to a management server using the `envoy.service.health.v3.HealthDiscoveryService.StreamHealthCheck` bidirectional streaming RPC.\n\n## Base Health Checker\n\n`source/common/upstream/health_checker_impl.h` includes the gRPC health proto definitions and serves as the base for all health checker implementations.\n\nThis implementation fully complies with the gRPC health checking protocol (grpc.health.v1.Health service) as defined in the gRPC specification, with proper handling of HealthCheckRequest messages, HealthCheckResponse status enums (SERVING, NOT_SERVING, SERVICE_UNKNOWN, UNKNOWN), and HTTP-to-gRPC status mapping for protocol translation."
}

